              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "LINAC"
                ],
                "institute": "2ITYLNS"
              },
              "free_text": [
                "  the accelerator complex located at",
                "the Laboratori Nazionali di Legnaro, which consists of",
                "the XTU Tandem and the super-conducting LINAC ALPI",
                "used as post-accelerator."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A Th-232 self-supporting target of 1.5 mg/cm**2",
                "thickness was used."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SI",
                "CSICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Detector was the 8-PiLP device, with",
                " 260 delta-E-E telescopes, consisting of two parts-",
                "the 'WALL' and the 'BALL'. Each telescope is made of a",
                "transmission type 300 mum thick Si detector followed by",
                "a CsI(Tl) crystal, 15 mm or 5 mm thick for the 'WALL'",
                "and the 'BALL'. The 'WALL' is a matrix of 11*11",
                "telescopes. The 'BALL' consists of 6 rings of 18",
                "telescopes each.",
                "The 'BALL' detectors were used to detect fission",
                "fragments as well as light charged particles.",
                "Two neutron detectors were operated in coincidence with",
                "the fission fragments. Neutron detectors are of",
                "cylindrical shape, 10 cm diameter and 5 cm thick,",
                "filled with NE213 liquid scintillator.",
                "Neutrons and gamma-rays were distinguished by a",
                "combination of time of flight and pulse shape",
                "discrimination techniques."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ADD-RES": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COMP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ".Dynamical model calculation.",
                "The pre-scission and post-scission neutron",
                "multiplicities are deduced to be 8.7+-2.0 and",
                " 9.4 +-2.0, respectively. The corresponding",
                "multiplicity values for  alpha particles are found",
                "to be 0.22 +-0.08 and  0.1+-0.03."
              ]
            }
          ],
